Key Match Events: Christian Eriksen scored a stunning late winner to give Denmark a 2-1 victory over Sweden.
Pierre-Emile Højbjerg scored the opening goal for Denmark in the 2nd minute.
Alexander Isak equalized for Sweden in the 9th minute.
Pre-Game Insights: Sweden's Danish coach Jon Dahl Tomasson was inducted into the Danish football Hall Of Fame ahead of kickoff.
Post-Match Reflections: Denmark coach Kasper Hjulmand gave credit to Tomasson for his work with Sweden.
Hjulmand mentioned that Denmark gave away too many turnovers in the first half.
Christian Eriksen expressed happiness for his assist for the opening goal and mentioned it created calm in the team.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was a pre-Euro 2024 friendly held at a sold-out Parken stadium in Copenhagen.
Denmark will face Slovenia, England, and Serbia in Group C of Euro 2024.
